<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">BMH</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Back in the spring of=C2=A02020, when the worl=
d was largely shut down for Covid-19, I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/29427655.285505/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDQtMzAvaWYteW91LXJlLWJvcmVkLXlvdS1jYW4tdHJhZGUt=
c3RvY2tzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTkyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3N=
vdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAxOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc321fb95" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  wrote</a> about what I <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29427655.285505/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDUtMjYvZ29sZG1hbi1=
3YXMtanVzdC10cnlpbmctdG8taGVscD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMDE5MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbW=
VkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjEwMTkmdXRtX2Nhb=
XBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB77c387cd" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  called<=
/a>=C2=A0the Boredom Markets Hypothesis,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D=
"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-=
block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>=C2=A0which was basically that retail traders like to trade stocks when=
 that is relatively more entertaining than their other entertainment option=
s. Some vague directional predictions of the BMH are:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">When stocks go up a lot, trading stoc=
ks is more entertaining than when they are flat or down.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">When most in-person entertainment options, live sp=
orts, etc., are shut down due to pandemic, trading stocks on your phone is =
relatively more entertaining than it would be in normal times.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">When people have more=C2=A0<em>time=C2=A0</em>=
to consume entertainment =E2=80=94=C2=A0because they are not working, or wo=
rking from home and not commuting, or working from home and not working ver=
y hard =E2=80=94=C2=A0there will be more demand for entertainment, includin=
g trading stocks.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">When the technol=
ogy for trading stocks is more entertaining =E2=80=94=C2=A0when you can do =
it on your phone, when the trading app feels like a game, when you get anim=
ated confetti for doing a trade =E2=80=94=C2=A0people will trade more stock=
s.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">When the=C2=A0<em>financi=
al=C2=A0</em>technology is more entertaining =E2=80=94=C2=A0when you can tr=
ade weekly-expiry single-stock options instead of just regular stocks =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0people will also trade more.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom:=
 5px;">When competing entertainment technology is more entertaining =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0when there=E2=80=99s lots of good television, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
people will do less stock trading.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>When competing=C2=A0<em>financial=C2=A0</em>technology is more entertainin=
g =E2=80=94=C2=A0when there=E2=80=99s legal sports gambling, crypto, etc. =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0people will do less stock trading.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The rough BMH story of the spring of 2020 was =
=E2=80=9Cthe stock market crashed due to collapsing business earnings, whic=
h would ordinarily drive retail investors out of the market because a crash=
ing market is no fun, but nothing else was very fun either, so retail inves=
tors flocked=C2=A0<em>to=C2=A0</em>the stock market, which led to a sharp r=
ebound in prices and, like, meme stocks.=E2=80=9D I don=E2=80=99t pretend t=
hat this is a particularly rigorous story or that it makes very clear predi=
ctions. But I don=E2=80=99t think it was especially=C2=A0<em>wrong</em>.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway since then the world has reopened and t=
he market has fallen again, so things are not much fun, and <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29427655.285505/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud=
3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9kYXktdHJhZGVycy1nby1iYWNrLXRvLXRoZWlyLWRheS1qb2JzLWFz=
LXN0b2NrLW1hcmtldC1zd29vbnMtMTE2NjYxNDgwOTQ_bW9kPWhwX2xlYWRfcG9zMg/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB3738d7b3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the Wall Street Journal reports</a>:</p=
>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The pandemic day-trading boom has gone bust.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A swooning stock market and high inflation hav=
e sapped individual investors=E2=80=99 enthusiasm for buying and selling st=
ocks. That was on display in earnings reports and financial disclosures fro=
m some of the biggest retail brokerages in recent weeks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The average daily number of retail trades hand=
led by Charles Schwab Corp. fell to 5.52 million in the third quarter, the =
lowest level since it acquired TD Ameritrade Holding Corp. in late 2020. At=
 Morgan Stanley, retail traders placed an average of 805,000 trades a day i=
n the third quarter. That was down 16% from a year earlier and the lowest l=
evel since the investment bank bought E*Trade Financial Corp. in late 2020.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those activity levels are well off highs notch=
ed at the zenith of the meme-stock era, when individual investors drove ral=
lies in the share prices of companies including GameStop Corp. In the first=
 quarter of 2021, Schwab reported 8.41 million daily average trades, while =
Morgan Stanley reported 1.62 million. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At Robinhood Markets Inc., the go-to trading a=
pp for young investors, July was the weakest month for average daily volume=
 for stocks and options trading in company records going back to March 2021=
. The company saw a slight rebound in August, the most recent month for whi=
ch data are available.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also here=E2=80=99s this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Robinhood Chief Executive Vlad Tenev said at t=
he September investor conference that the company=E2=80=99s customers care =
about different things this year compared with one or two years ago, citing=
 Google Trends searches as a good proxy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9C2020 and 2021, people were really int=
erested in investing in stocks,=E2=80=9D Mr. Tenev said. =E2=80=9CThere was=
 widespread participation in the stock market. Now people are talking about=
 gas prices and inflation.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I hope that that is how Robinhood does product=
 design. =E2=80=9CWhat are people Googling,=E2=80=9D I hope Robinhood asks,=
 =E2=80=9Cand how can we give them that in the form of an entertaining fina=
ncial product?=E2=80=9D I hope they=E2=80=99re going to introduce inflation=
 futures and binary options on oil prices. If you are in the entertainment =
business, you have to keep up with the trends.</p>
